spec: as3451
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 677 (as3451): __getitem__, __setitem__, __delitem__ dict-presence checks for asyncio types."
    - "Theme: __getitem__/__setitem__/__delitem__ dict-presence (obj[key], obj[key]=val, del obj[key])."
    - "All values False — these types do not implement the container/mapping access protocol in their own __dict__."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: asyncio.Task, asyncio.Future, asyncio.Event, asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Semaphore, asyncio.BoundedSemaphore, asyncio.Condition, asyncio.Queue, asyncio.PriorityQueue, asyncio.LifoQueue."
    - "Key finding (__getitem__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __getitem__. obj[key] delegates to __getitem__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. asyncio types do not define __getitem__ in their own __dict__ — subscript access is not part of the public API for any asyncio synchronization primitive, task, or queue type. asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles with no custom __getitem__ in their own __dict__. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: boolean-state and permit-count guards with no __getitem__ defined at the class level. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores accessed via get()/put() coroutines, not subscript; no __getitem__ in their own __dict__."
    - "Key finding (__setitem__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __setitem__. obj[key]=val delegates to __setitem__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. asyncio types do not define __setitem__ in their own __dict__; no item assignment is supported for these types. asyncio.Task/Future: result and cancellation are managed via explicit method calls (set_result(), cancel()); no __setitem__ defined in their own __dict__. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: synchronization guards with no __setitem__ defined in their own __dict__. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores with no __setitem__ in their own __dict__."
    - "Key finding (__delitem__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __delitem__. del obj[key] delegates to __delitem__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. asyncio types define no container/mapping deletion protocol in their own __dict__. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: queue items are dequeued via get(), not deleted by key; no __delitem__ in their own __dict__. asyncio.Task/Future/Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: none define __delitem__ in their own __dict__."
    - "Continues the all-false run from wave 656 (__call__/__len__/__getitem__) through wave 677 (__getitem__/__setitem__/__delitem__) — twenty-two consecutive waves of 100% false results for asyncio types."
    - "Note: wave 656 (as3136) first tested __getitem__ for asyncio types and found it false. Wave 657 (as3151) first tested __setitem__ and __delitem__ for asyncio types and found them false. This wave re-examines all three together as a focused container/mapping access protocol sweep."
    - "Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects:"
    - "  Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 657 (as3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 658 (as3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 659 (as3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 660 (as3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 661 (as3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 662 (as3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 663 (as3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 664 (as3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 665 (as3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 666 (as3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 667 (as3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 668 (as3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 669 (as3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 670 (as3346): __neg__/__pos__/__abs__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 671 (as3361): __invert__/__floor__/__ceil__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 672 (as3376): __trunc__/__round__/__index__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 673 (as3391): __int__/__float__/__complex__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 674 (as3406): __bool__/__str__/__repr__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 675 (as3421): __hash__/__eq__/__lt__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 676 (as3436): __le__/__gt__/__ge__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 677 (as3451): __getitem__/__setitem__/__delitem__ — all false for all 10."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __getitem__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__getitem__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __getitem__.
# obj[key] delegates to __getitem__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# asyncio types do not define __getitem__ in their own __dict__ — subscript
#   access is not part of the public API for any asyncio type.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles accessed via result(),
#   exception(), cancel(); no __getitem__ in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state synchronization guards with
#   no __getitem__ in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-count guards with no __getitem__
#   defined at the class level in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores accessed via get()/put()
#   coroutines; no __getitem__ in their own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

