# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __setitem__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__setitem__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __setitem__.
# obj[key]=val delegates to __setitem__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# asyncio types do not define __setitem__ in their own __dict__; item
#   assignment is not supported as part of the asyncio public API.
# asyncio.Task/Future: results are set via set_result()/set_exception();
#   no __setitem__ defined in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: synchronization state managed via
#   set()/clear()/acquire()/release(); no __setitem__ in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-count guards with no __setitem__
#   defined at the class level in their own __dict__.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores with no __setitem__
#   in their own __dict__; items are enqueued via put() coroutines.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

